# Styling Conventions (Tailwind v4)

## Source of truth

- Global styles: `packages/ui/src/styles/globals.css`
- Apps import: `import "@ryx/ui/globals.css"` in `main.tsx`
- Scan paths: `@source` in globals.css (include `apps/*/index.html` + `src/**`)

## Prefer utilities over @apply

- **Default**: utility classes in JSX via `cn()`
- **@apply**: only for repeated multi-class combos in `globals.css` `@layer components` (≥3 uses)
- **Never** `@apply` in app files; keep extraction in ui package

## Design tokens

Add tokens in `globals.css`:

```css
@theme inline {
  --color-brand: var(--brand);
}
:root {
  --brand: oklch(...);
}
```

Use semantic tokens (`bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`) — not raw hex in components.

## Tailwind v4 structure

- `@import "tailwindcss"` — entry
- `@theme inline` — design tokens
- `@layer base` — element defaults
- `@custom-variant` — `pad:`, `pc:`, `pointer-coarse:`, `hover-hover:`

Do not add `tailwind.config.ts` unless a tool requires it; shadcn v4 uses empty config in `components.json`.

## shadcn components

- Add to `packages/ui` via `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <name>` in ui package
- Compose with `cn()` for variants; extend via `className` prop
